# 🌌 Planet Visual Mapping System

## Purpose

Turn every GitHub repository into a living planet whose appearance evolves from real repo data.

This is a visual layer on top of the existing truth layer:
- repositories
- quests
- focus state
- lore
- activity

The 3D system must never replace the accessible 2D Hub. It enhances it.

---

## Core Rule

All planet visuals are derived from data, not random decoration.

---

## Data Inputs

- `language`
- `topics`
- `stars`
- `forks`
- `watchers`
- `openIssues`
- `closedIssuesRecent`
- `pushedAt`
- `questCount`
- `releaseCount`
- `archived`
- `focusState`
- `lorePresence`

---

## Planet Visual Output

```ts
export type PlanetVisual = {
  baseColor: string;
  accentColor: string;
  biome: string;
  radius: number;
  atmosphereIntensity: number;
  cloudCoverage: number;
  ringPresence: boolean;
  ringDensity: number;
  moonCount: number;
  surfaceRoughness: number;
  surfaceMetalness: number;
  lavaActivity: number;
  orbitRadius: number;
  orbitSpeed: number;
  axialTilt: number;
  spinSpeed: number;
  glowIntensity: number;
  questBeacons: number;
  stormIntensity: number;
  haloPulse: number;
};
```

---

## Mapping Rules

### Language → biome and palette

- TypeScript / JavaScript / React / Next.js → `neon-megacity`
- Python / AI / agents → `orbital-hub`
- Docs / learning / markdown-heavy repos → `crystalline-library`
- 3D / CAD / print / maker repos → `industrial-foundry`
- Art / animation / media → `creative-workshop`
- Unknown / mixed → `uncharted-world`

### Stars

- Increase `radius`
- Increase `glowIntensity`
- Use logarithmic scaling so large repos do not become absurdly huge

### Forks

- Increase `moonCount`
- Clamp between 0 and 5

### Open issues

- Increase `stormIntensity`
- Increase `lavaActivity`
- Add visual instability

### Recently closed issues

- Reduce `stormIntensity`
- Reduce `lavaActivity`
- Increase surface calmness

### Focus state

- `NOW` → brighter, closer orbit, faster spin
- `NEXT` → medium glow, medium orbit
- `RESTING` → dimmer, slower, farther out

### Quest count

- Increase `questBeacons`
- More quests = more visible mission lights on surface/night side

### Releases

- Temporary `haloPulse`
- Optional celebration ring or flare

### Archived

- Freeze motion
- Lower glow
- Lower spin
- Cooler, dormant palette

### Lore present

- Unlock handcrafted overrides
- Custom landmarks, civilisation name, special colour adjustments

---

## Accessibility Rules

- 3D is optional, not required to use the product
- Every planet must remain selectable from keyboard
- `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` disables orbit motion, storms, auto camera, and pulsing
- The 2D info panel remains the source of readable detail

---

## Scene Layout

- Inner shell: `NOW`
- Middle shell: `NEXT`
- Outer shell: `RESTING`

This keeps the most relevant worlds visually closest.

---

## Product Principle

The Living Hub is not a screensaver.

The purpose of Hyper 3D is:
1. make active work feel alive
2. make continuity emotionally rewarding
3. turn repo activity into visible world evolution
